Supervised Learning : Supervised Learning is a type of Machine Learning in which the model learns from labeled data. Labeled data means the correct output (target) is already known.
                      The model learns the relationship between input features and the target, then predicts the output for new data.
Types of Supervised Learning : 
Regression: Predicts numerical values (e.g., salary, house price).
Classification: Predicts categories (e.g., Yes/No, Spam/Not Spam).
Uses : 1. Easy to train with labeled data.
       2. Widely used in prediction problems.
       3. Provides accurate results when good-quality data is available.
Regression : Regression is a supervised learning technique used to predict continuous numerical values.
             Example : Predict employee salary, Predict house price.
Regression Algorithms : 1. Linear Regression
                        2. Ridge Regression
                        3. Lasso Regression
Classification : Classification is a supervised learning technique used to predict categories or classes.
                 Example : Spam or Not Spam, Pass or Fail
Classification Algorithms : 1. K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
                            2. Decision Tree
                            3. Naive Bayes
Evaluation Metrics : Evaluation metrics are measures used to check how well a Machine Learning model performs.
           For Regression Model :  Mean Squared Error (MSE), R² Score
           For Classification Model : Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, Confusion Matrix
Train-Test Split : Train-Test Split is the process of dividing the dataset into two parts:
Training Data: Used to train the model.
Testing Data: Used to evaluate the model.
Cross-Validation : Cross-validation is a technique used to evaluate a model more reliably by dividing the dataset into multiple parts (folds). 
                   The model is trained and tested several times, and the average performance is calculated.

